Welcome to OpenJDK 1.7 for OS/X
-------------------------------

The goal of this project is to provide a Java SE 1.7 to OS/X, using OpenJDK 1.7.

Project is hosted on GoogleCode, http://code.google.com/p/openjdk-osx-build/ and you will find there OS/X build and templates files.

OpenJDK 1.7 source code is available on OpenJDK mercurial repositories :

Initial version for OS/X was OpenJDK 1.7 from OpenBSD branch : http://hg.openjdk.java.net/bsd-port/bsd-port

There is now a Mac OS/X branch : http://hg.openjdk.java.net/macosx-port/macosx-port

Our project will allow you to build OpenJDK from both branches.

Have fun with OpenJDK on OS/X !

Issues
------

Even if OpenJDK VMs are seen by system and available on Java Preferences, you couldn't use as default VM.
See http://code.google.com/p/openjdk-osx-build/issues/detail?id=4

You could still use OpenJDK VM but you should specify the full PATH for java command, ie

OpenJDK 1.7 64bits from OpenBSD port :

/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/openjdk-1.7-x86_64/Contents/Home/bin/java

OpenJDK 1.7 32/64bits JDK from OS/X Mac port :

/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/1.7.0.jdk/Contents/Home/bin

OpenJDK 1.7 32/64bits JRE from OS/X Mac port :

/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/1.7.0.jre/Contents/Home/bin

